social_posts.post_text: The chief of police in #moscow sat down with me. A father of college aged kids himself and like many on the force is a graduate of the @uidaho this case has stunned the department and the City. He Maintains this was a targeted attack but won’t say exactly who or what was targeted. They continue looking into reports that Kaylee Goncalves possibly had a stalker. He also says that why they believe this was targeted is crucial to the investigation and why they won’t reveal. What the officers saw that day “shocks the conscious,” he said. He also vows to not let this case go cold @abcnews @goodmorningamerica @timmytusa

I have learned so much more in the past few months … how his colleagues in the PHD program at WSU viewed him … the “Bryan Talley” they kept to document his behavior- mainly when he was late or missed a female professors class.
